Signal
======

Lightweight modular audio patcher and MDU-based dynamic module loader.

Quick overview
--------------
- Loads `.mdu` module definition files at runtime, compiles them to shared objects, and dynamically links them into the app.
- File-watcher detects added/modified/removed `.mdu` files and (un)loads modules automatically.
- Uses ImGui/imnodes/implot for the UI and real-time audio via an internal audio callback.

Build
-----
This project uses CMake. To build:

```bash
mkdir -p build && cd build
cmake ..
cmake --build .
```

Run
---
After building the executable (`Signals` in the `build` folder), run the binary. You may want to set the module search paths via environment variable before launching:

```bash
export SIGNAL_MDU_PATHS=/path/to/your/modules:/another/path
./build/Signals
```

MDU template & default path
---------------------------
- The app can create a template `.mdu` file from the **File → Create template MDU** menu.
- By default the template will be written to `~/Documents/Signal/TemplateModule.mdu` when available; the app falls back to the current working directory otherwise.
- You can configure a custom template target with **File → Set MDU template path** and open the folder with **File → Open template folder**.

Searching for modules
---------------------
- At startup the app searches candidate runtime folders for `.mdu` files. To override the search list, set the `SIGNAL_MDU_PATHS` environment variable (colon/semicolon separated) or add paths in the **File → Set MDU Search Paths** menu.

Development notes
-----------------
- The module loader compiles `.mdu` sources with `g++` at runtime; the compiler must be available.
- ModuleLoader stores a cache (`build/mdu_cache` by default) for temporary shared objects.
- Handlers and UI are in `src/Handler.cpp`; MDU tooling is in `src/MDU/` and headers live under `include/MDU/`.

Contributing
------------
Contributions welcome. Open an issue or PR on the project repository and include a short description and reproduction steps.

